  "summary": "truffle-js postinstall executes curl via child_process at install time",
  "details": "The package.json lifecycle script invokes require('child_process').execSync with a curl command at install time. Running curl through child_process during an npm install lifecycle hook causes any installer to execute remote content fetched over the network, without consent, as soon as `npm install` runs. The package name also resembles the widely-used 'truffle' Ethereum development toolkit, consistent with a typosquat lure. There is no legitimate reason for a small utility package to shell out to curl from its package.json install hook.",
